00:24:22.910 --> 00:24:26.120
And so I think with moral
rights, and what I just want

00:24:26.120 --> 00:24:27.930
to address for a
couple of minutes here,

00:24:27.930 --> 00:24:30.470
is that the key thing is when
we're focused on musicians

00:24:30.470 --> 00:24:33.820
and other creators when they are
creating what I call artifacts,

00:24:33.820 --> 00:24:37.800
a particular finished
work, a recorded song,

00:24:37.800 --> 00:24:39.620
a book that's going
to be published,

00:24:39.620 --> 00:24:41.760
an artwork that's
going to be released.

00:24:41.760 --> 00:24:45.490
And then the key is-- and it's
related to a project I'm working

00:24:45.490 --> 00:24:48.930
on right now funded
by CPIP actuall--

00:24:48.930 --> 00:24:50.410
looking at arguing

00:24:50.410 --> 00:24:54.130
that copyright should perhaps be
viewed is as much an incentive

00:24:54.130 --> 00:24:57.880
for publication for
